In a single program, multiple if-else conditions can be present. 

Syntax:-

if (condition) {

// code

} else {

// code

}

// code

if (condition) {

// code

} else {

// code

}

// code

We can consider the following example for understanding multiple if-else.

Let’s say person A will pass if he scores 50% and person B will pass if he scores 40%. We can solve this problem using multiple if-else.

#include<stdio.h>i

int main() {

int scoreA, scoreB;

scanf(“%d %d”, &scoreA, &scoreB);

if(scoreA >= 50){

printf(“A passed”);

} else {

printf(“A failed”);

}

if(scoreB >= 50){

printf(“B passed”);

} else {

printf(“B failed”);

}

return 0;

}
